{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CLQCuJpCPaDD6Sy5ufwghu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Slice 0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN — Regression test for axis-E independence\n2\t\n3\t## State at spawn\n4\t\n5\tTBD — orchestrator fills baseline SHA + worktree branch.\n6\t\n7\t## Required reading\n8\t\n9\t- `scripts/set-version.sh` — full file (412 lines). Key sections:\n10\t  - L74-101 `set_workspace_dep_axis_w_versions` (skips embedder-api).\n11\t  - L104-121 `set_workspace_dep_embedder_api_version` (axis-E only).\n12\t  - L163-177 `set_embedder_api_version`.\n13\t  - L261-366 `check_files` (axis-E enforcement: explicit `[package].version`,\n14\t    not `version.workspace = true`; workspace-deps pin matches axis-E).\n15\t  - L378-388 `--workspace` dispatch (calls only axis-W setters).\n16\t- `dev/design/release.md` § Version axes.\n17\t- `dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol.md` — axis-E independence\n18\t  rule + trait-surface-change criterion.\n19\t- Wake decision `d-001` — axis-E pin behavior.\n20\t- `dev/plans/prompts/11c-set-version.md` — phase 11c precedent for\n21\t  test shape.\n22\t\n23\t## Tasks\n24\t\n25\t1. **TDD RED.** Add (or extend) `scripts/test_set_version.sh` (or\n26\t   the equivalent test file under `tests/` — confirm location at\n27\t   spawn). Test simulates a `--workspace 0.6.1` invocation in a\n28\t   tmpdir copy of the manifests; asserts:\n29\t   - `Cargo.toml [workspace.package].version` flips to `0.6.1`.\n30\t   - `Cargo.toml [workspace.dependencies] fathomdb-embedder-api =\n31\t{ ..., version = \"0.6.0\" }` (axis-E pin **unchanged**).\n32\t   - `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder-api/Cargo.toml\n33\t[package].version = \"0.6.0\"` (axis-E unchanged).\n34\t   - Every other workspace crate's `[package].version =\n35\tworkspace = true` (no inline version drift).\n36\t   - `--check-files` exits 0 after the bump.\n37\t     Per design verification, the script already implements this\n38\t     correctly — so the test SHOULD be GREEN immediately. The RED\n39\t     step exists as the regression sentinel: if a future change to\n40\t     `set-version.sh` accidentally extends axis-W to embedder-api,\n41\t     this test catches it.\n42\t2. **TDD GREEN.** Script is unchanged; test passes against current\n43\t   behavior.\n44\t3. **Refactor.** None — the test is the deliverable.\n45\t4. Wire the test into `scripts/agent-verify.sh` (or the equivalent\n46\t   harness invocation chain) so CI exercises it on every commit.\n47\t\n48\t## Hard constraints\n49\t\n50\t- **No `set-version.sh` edits unless the test surfaces an actual\n51\t  bug.** Design verification (2026-05-22) confirms the script\n52\t  already enforces axis-E independence. If the test fails against\n53\t  current behavior, STOP and surface — bug to fix before BUMP.\n54\t- **No new ADR.** axis-E independence already locked in\n55\t  `ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol.md` + `d-001`.\n56\t\n57\t## Output\n58\t\n59\t`dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN-output.json`. Required fields:\n60\t\n61\t- `test_path`: where the new test lives.\n62\t- `test_initial_verdict`: \"GREEN\" (expected) | \"RED\" (surface bug).\n63\t- `agent_verify_wired`: bool.\n64\t\n65\t<!-- ORCHESTRATOR: spawn this slice via dev/design/orchestration.md\n66\t§ 2 mechanics; codex review per § 3 -->\n67\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4851922d-2a7d-4929-9e12-caa05c2d927b","uuid":"1d8988a7-ee5d-4187-abdc-201c546f4929","timestamp":"2026-05-24T20:49:55.263Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN-20260524T204950Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN.md","content":"# Slice 0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN — Regression test for axis-E independence\n\n## State at spawn\n\nTBD — orchestrator fills baseline SHA + worktree branch.\n\n## Required reading\n\n- `scripts/set-version.sh` — full file (412 lines). Key sections:\n  - L74-101 `set_workspace_dep_axis_w_versions` (skips embedder-api).\n  - L104-121 `set_workspace_dep_embedder_api_version` (axis-E only).\n  - L163-177 `set_embedder_api_version`.\n  - L261-366 `check_files` (axis-E enforcement: explicit `[package].version`,\n    not `version.workspace = true`; workspace-deps pin matches axis-E).\n  - L378-388 `--workspace` dispatch (calls only axis-W setters).\n- `dev/design/release.md` § Version axes.\n- `dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol.md` — axis-E independence\n  rule + trait-surface-change criterion.\n- Wake decision `d-001` — axis-E pin behavior.\n- `dev/plans/prompts/11c-set-version.md` — phase 11c precedent for\n  test shape.\n\n## Tasks\n\n1. **TDD RED.** Add (or extend) `scripts/test_set_version.sh` (or\n   the equivalent test file under `tests/` — confirm location at\n   spawn). Test simulates a `--workspace 0.6.1` invocation in a\n   tmpdir copy of the manifests; asserts:\n   - `Cargo.toml [workspace.package].version` flips to `0.6.1`.\n   - `Cargo.toml [workspace.dependencies] fathomdb-embedder-api =\n{ ..., version = \"0.6.0\" }` (axis-E pin **unchanged**).\n   - `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder-api/Cargo.toml\n[package].version = \"0.6.0\"` (axis-E unchanged).\n   - Every other workspace crate's `[package].version =\nworkspace = true` (no inline version drift).\n   - `--check-files` exits 0 after the bump.\n     Per design verification, the script already implements this\n     correctly — so the test SHOULD be GREEN immediately. The RED\n     step exists as the regression sentinel: if a future change to\n     `set-version.sh` accidentally extends axis-W to embedder-api,\n     this test catches it.\n2. **TDD GREEN.** Script is unchanged; test passes against current\n   behavior.\n3. **Refactor.** None — the test is the deliverable.\n4. Wire the test into `scripts/agent-verify.sh` (or the equivalent\n   harness invocation chain) so CI exercises it on every commit.\n\n## Hard constraints\n\n- **No `set-version.sh` edits unless the test surfaces an actual\n  bug.** Design verification (2026-05-22) confirms the script\n  already enforces axis-E independence. If the test fails against\n  current behavior, STOP and surface — bug to fix before BUMP.\n- **No new ADR.** axis-E independence already locked in\n  `ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol.md` + `d-001`.\n\n## Output\n\n`dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN-output.json`. Required fields:\n\n- `test_path`: where the new test lives.\n- `test_initial_verdict`: \"GREEN\" (expected) | \"RED\" (surface bug).\n- `agent_verify_wired`: bool.\n\n<!-- ORCHESTRATOR: spawn this slice via dev/design/orchestration.md\n§ 2 mechanics; codex review per § 3 -->\n","numLines":67,"startLine":1,"totalLines":67}}}
