{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013BLQERb9L5cun1Ba9MR9pZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the state:\n- Current axis-E version: `0.6.0`\n- Workspace deps pin for fathomdb-embedder-api: `0.6.0`\n\nThe spec wants a test that:\n1. Runs `--workspace 0.6.1` \n2. Asserts workspace version becomes `0.6.1`\n3. Asserts fathomdb-embedder-api in workspace.dependencies stays at `0.6.0`\n4. Asserts fathomdb-embedder-api/Cargo.toml [package].version = `0.6.0`\n\n\n5. Asserts every other workspace crate uses `version.workspace = true`\n6. Asserts `--check-files` exits 0\n\nLooking at the existing tests, test #2 covers most of this with version `9.9.9` but doesn't use the specific `0.6.1/0.6.0` values and doesn't explicitly verify the workspace.dependencies pin for fathomdb-embedder-api. Test #12 shows how `--embedder-api` and `--workspace` flags interact, setting Axis E to the specified version while propagating workspace changes to dependent crates.\n\nI need a new test (test #13) that uses the actual regression values `0.6.1` for the workspace and `0.6.0` for the embedder API to catch any future breakage in the pin behavior. The test restores the snapshot, runs `--workspace 0.6.1`, then verifies the workspace version bumps to `0.6.1` while the embedder API version stays pinned at `0.6.0`.\n\nI'm checking that the Cargo.toml has the embedder-api dependency explicitly set to `0.6.0` while all other crates use workspace versioning, and that the validation passes. But I'm realizing the spec's wording about the workspace version \"flipping to 0.6.1\" needs clarification—I need to confirm whether this is describing the expected behavior or if there's a subtle interaction I'm missing with how the pin persists during the workspace bump.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1583,"cache_read_inp