{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KMVzGQeVrATFtboFLE4HzM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the context I need. The existing tests in `test_set_version.sh` already cover much of this, but I need to add a specific test (test #13) for the `--workspace 0.6.1` scenario that uses the real version numbers. The test should:\n\n1. Start from the clean snapshot (which has workspace at 0.6.0 and axis-E at 0.6.0)\n2. Run `--workspace 0.6.1`\n3. Assert:\n   a. Workspace version is `0.6.1`\n   b. Axis-E version (fathomdb-embedder-api/Cargo.toml [package].version) is still `0.6.0`\n   c. workspace.dependencies pin for fathomdb-embedder-api remains `0.6.0`\n   d. All other crates properly use `version.workspace = true`\n   e. `--check-files` exits successfully\n\nI need to write the test case that validates the workspace.dependencies pin line in the root Cargo.toml and confirms all non-embedder-api crates are using workspace versioning correctly. Let me add test #13 to the existing test file.\n\nLooking back at test #12 more carefully, I'm checking that the `--workspace` flag updates all Axis-W pins to the new version while leaving the Axis-E pin (fathomdb-embedder-api) untouched. The test restores the state, sets the embedder-api to one version, then updates the workspace to another, and verifies each of the five crates has the correct workspace.dependencies pin... I'm seeing the real challenge now — in a practical scenario, both axis-E and workspace start at the same version (0.6.0), then workspace bumps to 0.6.1. The test needs to catch a regression where the function stops checking for the embedder-api dependency and incorrectly updates it along with the workspace version. So test 13 should start from the snapshot with both at 0.6.0, then run the workspace bump to 0.6.1 without manually changing axis-E first, verifying that the embedder-api pin stays at 0.6.0 while workspace moves to 0.6.1. Now I'm reviewing the complete list of crates in the workspace and checking what dependencies are pinned in the Cargo.toml file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1252,"cache_read_input_tokens":25101,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1252},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4851922d-2a7d-4929-9e12-caa05c2d927b","uuid":"d7a7bc9b-af35-4b35-9775-c7fcf2f0a085","request_id":"req_011CbN46CKCRP8JJBXjrGGYL"}
