{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01E5Vh7SeKybHD5N6JGXhsye","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Done — slice 0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN complete\n\n**Verdict: GREEN** — all 23 tests pass on first run, script unchanged.\n\n### What was added\n\n**`scripts/tests/test_set_version.sh` — test #13** (60 new lines), with 5 sub-assertions:\n\n| ID | Assertion |\n|----|-----------|\n| 13a | `[workspace.package].version` flips to `0.6.1` |\n| 13b | `fathomdb-embedder-api/Cargo.toml [package].version` stays `0.6.0` |\n| 13c | `[workspace.dependencies] fathomdb-embedder-api` pin stays `0.6.0` |\n| 13d | Every other workspace crate retains `version.workspace = true` |\n| 13e | `--check-files` exits 0 after the bump |\n\n### Why this test is novel vs. existing tests\n\nTests #2 and #12 couldn't catch the key failure mode. Test #2 uses `9.9.9` and doesn't assert the workspace.dependencies pin explicitly. Test #12 pre-sets axis-E to `2.2.2` *before* running `--workspace`, so both axes start at different values — a broken guard that bumps `0.6.0→0.6.1` on embedder-api would be invisible. **Test #13 starts both axes at `0.6.0` and asserts the exact retained value `0.6.0`** — the only test that catches this.\n\n### CI wiring\n\nAlready wired: `scripts/agent-test.sh` → `run_capped test-set-version bash scripts/tests/test_set_version.sh` (no changes to agent-test.sh needed; it runs the whole file).\n\n### Output artifact\n\n`dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-AXIS-E-PIN-output.json` — `test_initial_verdict: \"GREEN\"`, `agent_verify_wired: true`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":566,"cache_read_input_tokens":34495,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":566},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4